race.comment: NEAP TIDE (2) got Pike and spiked his figures, belting the Northam Maidens but 5.2L over 2200m. He's showing plenty of promise for the Durrant yard, and Pike stays with him. Hard fit now and can take the next step. GUNS AWAY (1) rates a big threat. Stepped up to a middle distance at Belmont when narrowly beaten, and then tackled much tougher than this beaten 2.2L at Ascot. That more than stacks up, and he can bounce. INTO THE FUTURE (5) was up from a mile and won a Northam Maiden as expected. This is tougher, but he will use the handy gate and is in well again with the 3kg claim. AUTHORATIVE (4) went well at Ascot but was plainer at Northam following when she didn't manage the wide barrier. Has some weight relief and should be around the mark.
